Reasoning: The paper discusses distributed systems, databases, and computation over eventually consistent information, which are all topics that fall under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Databases (cs.DB), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on databases and their optimization, cs.DB is the most likely category, followed by cs.DC and cs.DS. The paper also touches on software engineering and system design, which could place it in cs.SE and cs.SY, respectively.
